Design inspiration (no code incorporated)
================================================================================

3. Muon optimizer — Keller Jordan et al.
   https://github.com/KellerJordan/Muon
   The original Muon optimizer (momentum orthogonalization via Newton-Schulz
   iteration) that DMuon provides a distributed implementation of.

4. Moonlight — "Muon is Scalable for LLM Training", Moonshot AI (Kimi)
   https://github.com/MoonshotAI/Moonlight
   Copyright (c) Moonshot AI.
   DMuon's distributed design, and the weight-decay and update-scale
   adjustments that make Muon a drop-in AdamW replacement, are inspired by
   Moonlight's ZeRO-1 Muon implementation.

5. PyTorch — FSDP2 (fully_shard, MixedPrecisionPolicy)
   https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch
   Copyright (c) Meta Platforms, Inc. and affiliates, and the PyTorch
   contributors. Licensed under the BSD-3-Clause license.
   DMuon composes with PyTorch's FSDP2 and mirrors the semantics and naming of
   its mixed-precision and sharding APIs (e.g. param_dtype, cast_forward_inputs,
   reshard_after_forward).
